Police have arrested two men after more than 300 cannabis plants were found on a farm.Dorset Police entered four addresses in the Shaftesbury area on the morning of 29 April and seized a haul of plants and equipment.A man in his 40s was held on suspicion of cultivating a Class B drug and was later released pending further inquiries.A man in his 50s was also arrested on suspicion of producing a Class B drug and remains in custody.
The force urged people to contact them if they have any information.
